<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  	<head>
	  <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
    <style type="text/css">
      li.bat:hover {color: purple;}
      .foo:hover {color: red;}
      #bar:hover, #bar2:hover, #bar3:hover {color: blue;}
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>Here is the style declaration for this page:</p>
    <blockquote><pre><code>
      &lt;style type="text/css">
        li.bat:hover {color: purple;}
        .foo:hover {color: red;}
        #bar:hover, #bar2:hover, #bar3:hover {color: blue;}
      &lt;/style>
    </code></pre></blockquote>
  
    <ul>
      <li id="bar" class="foo" style="color: green">
        <code>&lt;li id="bar" class="foo" style="color: green"></code> This line is green because inline styles override &lt;style> blocks (which override stylesheets).
       </li>
    </ul>

    <p>Hover your mouse over the rest of these lines to see the answer, but try and guess the answer first!</p>
  
    <ul>
      <li id="bar2" class="foo">
        what color am I? <code>&lt;li id="bar2" class="foo"></code> 
      </li>

      <li id="bar3"><span class="foo">
        what color am I? <code>&lt;li id="bar3">&lt;span class="foo"></code>
      </span></li>

      <li class="foo bat">
        what color am I? <code>&lt;li class="foo bat"></code>
      </li>
  
    </ul>
    
    <p><a href="index.html">&larr; Back to the Documentation Index</a></p>        
  </body>
</html>


